# NumPy-Style Docstrings

Always show full docstring when editing any Python function or class.
If missing, create NumPy-style docstring with **Summary / Parameters / Returns / Examples**.

## Format Template

```python
def function_name(param1: type, param2: type) -> return_type:
    """Short summary of function purpose.
    
    Longer description explaining the function's behavior,
    edge cases, and important details.
    
    Parameters
    ----------
    param1 : type
        Description of first parameter
    param2 : type
        Description of second parameter
        
    Returns
    -------
    return_type
        Description of return value
        
    Examples
    --------
    >>> function_name(value1, value2)
    expected_result
    """
```

## Class Docstrings

```python
class ClassName:
    """Short summary of class purpose.
    
    Longer description of the class, its purpose, and usage.
    
    Attributes
    ----------
    attribute1 : type
        Description of attribute1
    attribute2 : type
        Description of attribute2
        
    Methods
    -------
    method_name(param)
        Brief description of what method does
    """
```

## Requirements
- Every public function/class must have a docstring
- Include parameter types and descriptions
- Document return values
- Add usage examples when helpful
- Keep summary line under 79 characters
